100
00:04:37,620 --> 00:04:41,300
Today’s question comes from William Adderholdt.

101
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:43,910
“I have a question for the show.

102
00:04:43,910 --> 00:04:45,560
What exactly are these "live markets"

103
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,760
where the epidemic supposedly started?

104
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:50,050
How unsanitary are they?”

105
00:04:50,050 --> 00:04:51,050
Good question.

106
00:04:51,050 --> 00:04:54,220
These markets are often called “wet markets”
in Chinese.

107
00:04:54,220 --> 00:04:55,840
They’re usually open air markets

108
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,431
where you can buy food from different vendors.

109
00:04:57,431 --> 00:05:00,200
And they sell everything from fruits and vegetables

110
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:03,440
to raw meat, seafood, and live animals.

111
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:06,390
They’re a huge part of China’s food supply
chain.

112
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:09,860
And some of them are...not super sanitary.

113
00:05:09,860 --> 00:05:11,900
Chopping fish on the floor.

114
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:14,580
Butchering pork without gloves.

115
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:18,090
And freshly slaughtered chickens just hanging
around.

116
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:20,850
This is the Huanan Seafood Market in Wuhan—

117
00:05:20,850 --> 00:05:23,210
regarded as the epicenter of the outbreak.

118
00:05:23,210 --> 00:05:25,140
It’s been closed down now.

119
00:05:25,140 --> 00:05:27,670
They sold all sorts of weird stuff.

120
00:05:27,670 --> 00:05:32,170
This was a menu at one of the more...exotic
animal stalls.

121
00:05:32,170 --> 00:05:34,030
To be fair, according to some reports,

122
00:05:34,030 --> 00:05:37,160
the *first* person reportedly infected with
the coronavirus—

123
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:41,050
on December 1—never came into contact with
that wet market.

124
00:05:41,050 --> 00:05:43,350
There’s a lot of conflicting information
right now

125
00:05:43,350 --> 00:05:46,400
and it will be months before we know what
happened.

126
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:49,910
But the virus did somehow spread *to* that
market.

127
00:05:49,910 --> 00:05:53,520
And wet markets are the perfect place to spread
disease.

128
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,300
Because they’re pretty much unregulated

129
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,540
and having live animal feces,

130
00:05:57,540 --> 00:05:58,540
blood from slaughtered animals,

131
00:05:58,540 --> 00:06:03,230
and fresh produce all next to each other is
extremely unsanitary.

132
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:06,560
But what doesn’t kill you makes you stronger,
right?

133
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:08,040
Thanks for your question.

